996 |url= |location=London |publisher=Ebury Press |page= |date=25 April 1996 |isbn=978-0091814625}}\n*{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=The Best of Masterchef |url= |location=London |publisher=Ebury Press |page= |date=2 January 1997 |isbn=978-0091853068}}\n*{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Masterchef: 1997 |url= |location=London |publisher=Ebury Press |page= |date=3 April 1997 |isbn=978-0091853051}}\n*{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Junior Masterchef 1998 |url= |location=London |publisher=Ebury Press |page= |date=5 March 1998 |isbn=978-0091853228}}\n*{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Masterchef: Best of British Cooking |url= |location=London |publisher=Ebury Press |page= |date=7 January 1999 |isbn=978-0091868444}}\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[MasterChef: The Professionals]]''\n* ''[[Junior MasterChef]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BBC programme}}\n* {{UKGameshow|Masterchef}}\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b007mtf0 ''Celebrity MasterChef'']\n* {{IMDb title|0870973|Celebrity MasterChef}}\n* {{UKGameshow|Masterchef_Goes_Large|MasterChef Goes Large}}\n* {{IMDb title|0805418|MasterChef Goes Large}}\n\n{{MasterChef}}\n\n[[Category:BBC television game shows]]\n[[Category:British cooking television programmes]]\n[[Category:1990s British game shows]]\n[[Category:2000s British game shows]]\n[[Category:2010s British game shows]]\n[[Category:2020s British game shows]]\n[[Category:1990 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2001 British television series endings]]\n[[Category:2005 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:MasterChef|UK]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:British television series revived after cancellation]]\n[[Category:Television series by Endemol]]\n[[Category:1990s British cooking television series]]\n[[Category:2000s British cooking television series]]\n[[Category:2010s British cooking television series]]\n[[Category:2020s British cooking television series]]\n", "name_user": "Weboflight", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOriginal series", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MasterChef_(British_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "List of World War II aces from Japan", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of [[Flying ace|fighter ace]]s in [[World War II]] from [[Japan]], as officially credited by the [[Empire of Japan|Imperial Japanese]] government. For other countries see [[List of World War II aces by country]].\n{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}\n\n== Abbreviations ==\n* \"KIA\": [[Killed in action]] (dates are included where possible)\n* \"DOW\": [[Died of wounds]]\n* \"KIFA\": Killed in Flying Accident\n* \"MIA\": [[Missing in action]]\n* \"POW\": [[Prisoner of War]]\n* \"IJA\": [[Imperial Japanese Army]]\n* \"IJN\": [[Imperial Japanese Navy]]\n\n== A ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Kenichi Abe]] (\u963f\u90e8\u5065\u5e02) || 10 (five jointly) || Chief Petty Officer || IJN || || Survived World War II.<ref>Hata, p. 331</ref>\n|-\n| [[Takahide Aioi]] (\u76f8\u751f\u9ad8\u79c0) || 10 || Commander || IJN || || 5 of the victories during [[Second Sino-Japan War]]; later served as Vice Admiral in the [[Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force|JMSDF]]<ref>Hata, p. 339</ref>\n|-\n| [[Sadaaki Akamatsu]] (\u8d64\u677e\u8c9e\u660e) || 27 || Lieutenant Junior Grade || IJN || || 11 of the victories during [[Second Sino-Japan War]]<ref>Hata, p. 252; Sakaida, pp. 176\u2013178.</ref>\n|-\n| [[Satoru Anabuki]] (\u7a74\u5439\u667a) || 39 || Sergeant Major || IJA || || Later served as Lieutenant Colonel in the [[Japan Ground Self-Defense Force|JGSDF]]<ref>Sakaida, pp. 34\u201335.</ref>\n|-\n| Katsumi Anma (\u5b89\u9593 \u514b\u5df3) || 27 || || IJA || || KIA 8 April 1942\n|-\n| Yoshitugu Aramaki (\u8352\u8494 \u7fa9\u6b21) || 5 || || IJA || ||\n|-\n| Yoshisuke Arita (\u6709\u7530 \u7fa9\u52a9) || 5 || || IJN || ||\n|-\n| Mitsuzo Asai || 7 || || IJA || ||\n|-\n| Jiro Asano (\u6d45\u91ce \u4e8c\u90ce) || 10 || || IJA || ||\n|-\n| Tomita Atake (\u963f\u6b66 \u5bcc\u592a) || 10 || || IJN || ||\n|}\n\n== B ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n| Takeo\tBanno (\u962a\u91ce \u9686\u96c4) || 10 || || IJN || || KIA 7 October 1943\n|-\n| Kisaji Beppu || 5 || || IJA || || KIA 7.2.1942\n|}\n\n== C ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n|[[Jir\u014d Ch\u014dno]] || 7 || Ensign || IJN || || KIA 21 February 1941\n|}\n\n== E ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n| Yuichi Ema (\u6c5f\u99ac \u53cb\u4e00) || 6 || || IJN || || KIA 29 October 1944\n|-\n| Masuaki Endo (\u9060\u85e4 \u685d\u79cb) || 14 || || IJN || || KIA 7 June 1943\n|-\n| Sachio Endo (\u9060\u85e4 \u5e78\u7537) || 8 || || IJN || || KIA 14 January 1945\n|-\n| Toyoki Eto (\u6c5f\u85e4 \u8c4a\u6a39) || 12+1 shared +4 probable || || IJA || ||\n|}\n\n== F ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Iyozo Fujita]] (\u85e4\u7530\u6021\u4e0e\u8535) || 11 (42?)|| || IJN || ||\n|-\n| Kihei\tFujiwara (\u85e4\u539f \u559c\u5e73) || 5 || || IJN || ||\n|-\n| Sumio\tFukuda (\u798f\u7530 \u6f84\u592b) || 11 || || IJN || || KIA 24 October 1944\n|-\n| [[Yoshio Fukui]] || 11, 4 probable || Lieutenant || IJN || ||\n|-\n| Shigeo Fukumoto (\u798f\u672c \u7e41\u592b) || 72 || || IJN || ||\n|-\n| Yonesuke Fukuyama || 7 || || IJA || ||\n|-\n| Goro Furugori (\u53e4\u90e1 \u543e\u90ce) || 25+ || || IJA || || KIA 3 November 1944\n|-\n| Haruyoshi Furukawa (\u53e4\u6cb3 \u6625\u7fa9) || 5+ || || IJA || ||\n|}\n\n== G ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n| Hiroshi Gomi || 7 || || IJA || ||\n|-\n| Kurakazu Goto || 8 ||  || IJN || || KIA 9 September 1943\n|}\n\n== H ==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Name !! Kills !!  Rank !! Service !! Awards !! Notes\n|-\n| Matsuo Hagiri (\u7fbd\u5207 \u677e\u96c4) || 13 || || IJN || ||\n|-\n| Tomio Hanada (\u82b1\u7530 \u5bcc\u7537) || 25 || || IJA || ||\n|-\n| [[Watari Handa